Social Advocate Miss Lawrence to Host the Purpose Ball 

Miss Lawrence, the legendary Atlanta Mother of the iconic House of Balenciaga, is partnering with Pepsi, Live Nation Urban, and award-winning music artist Mary J. Blige to present The Purpose Ball: Bridging the Gap during this year’s Strength of a Woman Festival and Summit on Sunday, May 14 at The Bank in Atlanta, Georgia.

Created to honor the LGBTQ community’s undeniable impact on pop culture and celebrate the essence of ballroom culture, the Purpose Ball will feature special performances from Saucy Santana and special guest appearances from Blige herself, who is serving as a judge alongside Raven Goodwin and Dashaun Wesley of the Emmy-nominated HBO Max ballroom competition series Legendary. The ball will also gather notable members of the ballroom community and introduce rising stars from illustrious houses, all competing for one-of-a-kind prizes in different categories, a tradition from Harlem’s underground ball scene.

Aside from the Purpose Ball, the four-day festival and summit will include musical performances, a gospel brunch, and a comedy night.

Lawrence, who is known largely for his roles on productions like Bros, The United States vs. Billie Holiday, and The Real Housewives of Atlanta, will produce and curate the Purpose Ball and serve as the event’s Master of Ceremonies. He took some time to talk more about it with OFM.

“I may have walked my very first ball in 2006. As you know, it’s a very magnetic space. It’s a space where you can literally become whatever you want and anything you ever dreamed about. If that’s a supermodel, if that’s an entertainer, whatever, here’s a space where you can go, and depending on how well you do and how well you put your best foot forward, the entire space affirms you as that thing.” says Miss Lawrence 

Interview by @dennyp777 

For full interview link in bio.

Stay up-to-date with Lawrence by following him on Instagram @misslawrence. For additional details regarding the 2023 Strength of a Woman Festival and Summit and to purchase tickets for the Purpose Ball, visit soawfestival.com.

Photos courtesy of Miss Lawrence

This past Mother’s Day was a Historic one for me for 2 reasons, I lost my Father who became my heavenly Angel and I executed “The Purpose Ball” that I created and produced for @pepsi and @therealmaryjblige Strength of A Woman Festival powered by @livenationurban Sponsored by @gileadsciences . I’m always in aww of how God moves and I’ll always be grateful and give him the glory in all things. “The Purpose Ball” is an extension of Miss Lawrence’s Plated Purpose dinner and it was a huge success.  There are so many people that played a part in the success of the ball and while we acknowledge Pride Month and Juneteenth I find it appropriate to recognize the impact The Purpose Ball had. The Purpose was to aid in Bridging the gaps that divide the Hetero and LGBTQ communities of color. I worked closely with @livenationurban @theayarsagency @therealmaryjblige @gileadsciences and the Ballroom community to make this event a historic one, and we achieved it! While my heart was broken about my Father it was also very full at the same time seeing the amount of support the ball received. I will be posting a lot of clips from the ball during the rest of this month as well as a LEGENDARY JUNETEENTH CELEBRATION I’m attending! Oh and The Purpose Ball 2024 is already in its planning stages!!!!!See y’all soon ❤️🙏🏾❤️🙏🏾

Thank You @fox5atlanta for this piece on #GoodDayAtlanta …Beyoncé's album "Renaissance" stands as a heartfelt homage to the vibrant and rich culture of  Ballroom and the black LGBTQ community. In recent years, The House of Balenciaga has experienced numerous instances where our House and its members have been illuminated through their connections to this album and its tour. Most recently, this spotlight included our captivating vogue sensation, @Honeybalenciaga, the talented, @_nvme who graced the stage as one of Beyoncé background dancers, and @_iam_theone, who ignited the DC stage last weekend and Charlotte's earlier this week. It is essential to acknowledge Beyoncé's role spotlighting and elevating our ballroom culture.  Consequently, we proudly introduce a resolution that formally designates August 11th, 2023, as BEY DAY!
Our gratitude extends to the @cityofatlantaga, House of Representatives member @ParkCannon58 Councilman Hills, Overall Mother @shannonbalenciaga and our own superstar, @misslawrence; Legendary Atlanta Mother of the House of Balenciaga and the entire @houseofbalenciaga for their instrumental roles in making this resolution a reality.  Representation holds transformative power, shaping lives profoundly. In the wake of the tragic loss of O'Shae Sibley, who was fatally attacked for voguing a Brooklyn gas station, the significance of living authentically, truthfully, and unapologetically becom even more poignant. Our voices will not be silenced.  #Beyoncé #Renaissance #LGBTQBallroomCult
